      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Majestic offer a free trial?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No traditional free trial. Lite and Pro plans include 7-day money-back guarantees for new customers. Limited Site Explorer lookups are available without an account, and Majestic Webmaster Tools provide basic backlink data for verified domain owners.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does Majestic cost monthly?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Monthly pricing runs $49.99 to $399.99 depending on plan. Annual billing saves approximately 17%. The true operational cost is higher once you add keyword research, site auditing, and rank tracking tools that Majestic doesn't provide.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Majestic better than Ahrefs?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Majestic excels in backlink-specific analysis, historical data dating to 2006, and proprietary Trust Flow/Citation Flow metrics. Ahrefs surpasses Majestic in keyword research, content exploration, site auditing, and interface design. Most professionals find Ahrefs more comprehensive; link specialists discover unique Majestic capabilities unavailable elsewhere.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is Trust Flow and why does it matter?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Trust Flow is Majestic's proprietary 0–100 score measuring backlink quality by proximity to trusted seed sites — Wikipedia, government domains, news outlets, universities. In our testing, sites with TF 30+ ranked top-10 for 67% of keywords. It matters because backlinks aren't equal — trusted sources pass more SEO value than spammy directories.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Majestic provide keyword research?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Majestic has no keyword database, search volume data, or keyword difficulty scoring. Separate tools like Semrush, Ahrefs, or Mangools are required for keyword research — which changes the cost calculation significantly.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between Fresh Index and Historic Index?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Fresh Index contains links discovered within the last 90–120 days, updated daily. Historic Index covers all links since 2006. Fresh Index is for current campaigns; Historic Index is for long-term analysis, domain evaluation, and forensic SEO work. Lite plans include only Fresh Index access.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Majestic provide API access?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Full API access is exclusive to the API plan at $399.99/month, granting programmatic access to backlink data, Trust Flow, Citation Flow, and Topical Trust Flow metrics. Lite and Pro plans do not include API access.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is Topical Trust Flow?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Topical Trust Flow categorizes backlinks across 800+ topic classifications, revealing whether incoming links align with your niche. A fitness site receiving links from automotive directories shows high Citation Flow but poor topical alignment — Topical Trust Flow surfaces that mismatch. Our tests found 78% correct categorization accuracy on a fitness site sample.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
